      propertyPath: npcName
      value: Some Random Guy
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1708576647234818529, guid: 6bcbd75a4bd4dba45802087238127d31, type: 3}
      propertyPath: dialogBackButton
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 1682769453}
    - target: {fileID: 1708576647234818529, guid: 6bcbd75a4bd4dba45802087238127d31, type: 3}
      propertyPath: singleActivation
      value: 0
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1708576647234818529, guid: 6bcbd75a4bd4dba45802087238127d31, type: 3}
      propertyPath: dialog.Array.size
      value: 3
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1708576647234818529, guid: 6bcbd75a4bd4dba45802087238127d31, type: 3}
      propertyPath: 'dialog.Array.data[0]'
      value: ' Hello There!'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1708576647234818529, guid: 6bcbd75a4bd4dba45802087238127d31, type: 3}
      propertyPath: 'dialog.Array.data[1]'
      value: Please find and kill the 10 guys somewhere in the forest.
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1708576647234818529, guid: 6bcbd75a4bd4dba45802087238127d31, type: 3}
      propertyPath: 'dialog.Array.data[2]'
      value: Good Luck!
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1708576647234818529, guid: 6bcbd75a4bd4dba45802087238127d31, type: 3}
      propertyPath: 'dialog.Array.data[3]'
      value: Environment lets you add walls and furniture.
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1708576647234818529, guid: 6bcbd75a4bd4dba45802087238127d31, type: 3}
      propertyPath: 'dialog.Array.data[4]'
      value: "Logic are invisible objects that will advance the game, like \nrevealing
        something, playing a sound, or creating an objective."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1708576647234818529, guid: 6bcbd75a4bd4dba45802087238127d31, type: 3}
      propertyPath: 'dialog.Array.data[5]'
      value: Materials can be dragged onto objects to change their texture or color.
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1708576647234818529, guid: 6bcbd75a4bd4dba45802087238127d31, type: 3}
      propertyPath: 'dialog.Array.data[6]'
      value: Objects let you interact with things, push them, or pick them up.
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1708576647234818529, guid: 6bcbd75a4bd4dba45802087238127d31, type: 3}
      propertyPath: 'dialog.Array.data[7]'
      value: "There are also sound files that you can play in the game. \nWe don't
        have a lot of sounds in this game, since it was initially \nmade for a computer
        lab with no speakers."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1708576647234818529, guid: 6bcbd75a4bd4dba45802087238127d31, type: 3}
      propertyPath: 'dialog.Array.data[8]'
      value: "You can also create your own objects and logic through 3D modelling
        and coding, \nor import objects and code that other people have made."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1708576647234818529, guid: 6bcbd75a4bd4dba45802087238127d31, type: 3}
